    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen defining an LSP configuration in the standard config path as in `~/.config/nvim/lsp/` - it doesn't override the settings applied by third-party like nvim-lspconfig.\nI assume it's because the config root directory appears first in the `runtimepath` and thus nvim-lspconfig's configuration overrides whatever user defines.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nUser's configuration has higher priority over plugin-defined.\n\nAt the moment it can be fixed by placing configs in `after/lsp/`.\nBut I'm not sure whether it's the desired behavior and I think it's more intuitive to users to have their configs override everything else.",
