            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "That's what `~.config/nvim/after/lsp/` is for.\n\nSomewhere in a parallel universe `nvim-lspconfig` repo has something like this in their `README.md`:\n\n> If you don't want to install the plugin, you can copy any config directly from [lsp/](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/master/lsp) and put it in a local `lsp/` directory in your `'runtimepath'`. And if you want to keep your configs in separate files while `nvim-lspconfig` provides the defaults, put your own configs in `after/lsp/` instead.\n\ninstead of\n\n> You can also copy any config directly from [lsp/](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/master/lsp) and put it in a local lsp/ directory in your 'runtimepath'.\n\nand people don't report [this \"issue\"](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/36540) once a week :_)\n\nUnfortunately, <https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/35899> did not lead to anything. So, to someone reading this, if your English is good, could you please rephrase my suggestion into something adequate and make a much-needed PR ðŸ™\n\n---\n\n[edit]\n\nOr even explain it as a priority chain:\n\n```\nFrom lowest to highest priority:\nlsp/ (nvim-lspconfig uses this) -> after/lsp/ -> vim.lsp.config()\n``` ",
